---
import Shell from "../components/Shell.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<Shell
  title="Triad | global and pairwise identity"
  description="A small identity broker with provider-global, account, and per-app identifiers."
>
  <section class="hero shell">
    <p class="hero-signal">ONE LOGIN. THREE EXPLICIT IDS.</p>
    <h1>IDENTITY,<br /><span>THAT WORKS.</span></h1>
    <div class="hero-bottom">
      <p>
        One sign-in layer for browser, CLI, and device apps. Keep continuity across your products, or give
        every client its own private user ID.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/demo/">TRY TRIAD →</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/olstenlarck/triad-auth">VIEW SOURCE ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="provider-band" aria-label="Supported identity providers">
    <div class="shell provider-list">
      <span>GOOGLE</span><span>GITHUB</span><span>TWITTER</span><span>CODE + PKCE</span><span
        >DEVICE FLOW</span
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="identity-model shell" aria-labelledby="identity-title">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2 id="identity-title">ONE LOGIN.<br />NO IDENTITY GUESSING.</h2>
      <p>Email is profile data, not a key. Every token names exactly which identity contract it carries.</p>
    </div>
    <dl class="claim-ledger">
      <div>
        <dt>provider_sub</dt>
        <dd>pid_twitter_5a8f...</dd>
        <p>
          Provider-global and correlatable across Triad clients that receive it, without exposing the upstream
          ID.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>account_sub</dt>
        <dd>acc_4da6c809...</dd>
        <p>Broker-global. Correlates one Triad account across clients.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <dt>pairwise_sub</dt>
        <dd>pws_9c0e7b2a...</dd>
        <p>Stable inside one app. Different client, different identifier.</p>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="privacy-scopes shell" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2 id="privacy-title">ASK FOR LESS.<br />REVEAL LESS.</h2>
      <p>
        A client chooses its request. Triad shows the complete list before approval, and shares nothing beyond
        it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="privacy-contract">
      <article class="privacy-default">
        <span>DEFAULT REQUEST</span>
        <h3>IDENTITY ONLY</h3>
        <code>scope=openid</code>
        <p>No raw provider ID, email, handle, name, avatar, or provider access token.</p>
      </article>
      <div class="scope-manifest">
        <p>OPTIONAL PROFILE SCOPES</p>
        <dl>
          <div><dt>email</dt><dd>email + email_verified</dd></div>
          <div><dt>handle</dt><dd>preferred_username</dd></div>
          <div><dt>name</dt><dd>name</dd></div>
          <div><dt>avatar</dt><dd>picture</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="quickstart" class="quickstart shell" aria-labelledby="quickstart-title">
    <div class="section-heading compact">
      <h2 id="quickstart-title">POINT. REDIRECT. VERIFY.</h2>
      <p>Authorization Code + mandatory S256 PKCE. ES256 tokens. Standard JWKS.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="code-window" role="region" aria-label="Authorization request example" tabindex="0">
      <div class="code-meta"><span>GET /authorize</span><span>01 / 03</span></div>
      <pre><code>?client_id=triad-demo
&amp;provider=github
&amp;redirect_uri=http://localhost:4321/demo/callback/
&amp;code_challenge=...
&amp;code_challenge_method=S256</code></pre>
    </div>
    <ol class="flow-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Choose a provider.</strong><span
          >Triad maps its stable identity, then discards the provider access token.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Exchange once.</strong><span
          >Your app exchanges the short-lived code with its PKCE verifier.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Verify locally.</strong><span
          >Check ES256, issuer, audience, and expiry against the published JWKS.</span
        >
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="device-callout shell" aria-labelledby="device-title">
    <p class="device-code" aria-hidden="true">F7KQ-2M9X</p>
    <div>
      <h2 id="device-title">AUTHORIZE<br /><span>ANOTHER DEVICE.</span></h2>
      <p>
        Show a short code on the device. The user opens Triad in a browser, reviews the connection, and
        approves it.
      </p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/device/verify/">OPEN DEVICE VERIFICATION →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Shell>
